  "title": "Automation Engineer (MES | IoT | Semiconductor Fab)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Collaborate with vendors to evaluate, configure, and deploy communication systems between MES, semiconductor tools, and<strong> </strong>Autonomous Mobile Robot (AMR).</li><li>Design and develop intuitive web-based interfaces for system monitoring, operational control, and user interaction.</li><li>Generate automated reports, dashboards, analytics, and alerts to support real-time decision-making.</li><li>Conduct data integrity checks, implement automated failure alerts, troubleshoot system issues, and enhance automation frameworks.</li><li>Develop and maintain IoT automation systems for equipment data collection, cleaning, restructuring, and storage.</li><li>Create operator and equipment interfaces to streamline digital data entry.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Microelectronics, Electrical, Mechanical, Chemical Engineering, or related field.</li><li>Strong programming experience in <strong>PHP, JavaScript, Python</strong>, or other web technologies.</li><li>Familiarity with MES systems, SECS/GEM protocols, and AMHS is a plus.</li><li>1 to 3 years of experience in MES system administration, semiconductor process modules, equipment engineering, or digital transformation/automation.</li><li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.</li><li>Ability to collaborate with cross-functional teams and vendors.</li><li>Knowledge of IoT integration, data analytics, and industrial automation principles.</li></ul><p><br />To apply, please visit <a href=\"https://www.gmprecruit.com/job-search/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">www.gmprecruit.com</a> and search for Job Reference: <strong>63XW53VR</strong></p><p>To learn more about this opportunity, please contact Yingying at yingying.lai@gmprecruit.com</p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>GMP Technologies (S) Pte Ltd | EA Licence: 11C3793 | EA Personnel: Lai Yingying | Registration No: R1110239</p><p><em>This is in partnership with the Employment and Employability Institute Pte Ltd (e2i).</em></p><p><em>e2i is the empowering network for workers and employers seeking employment and employability solutions. e2i serves as a bridge between workers and employers, connecting with workers to offer job security through job-matching, career guidance and skills upgrading services, and partnering employers to address their manpower needs through recruitment, training, and job redesign solutions. e2i is a tripartite initiative of the National Trades Union Congress set up to support nation-wide manpower and skills upgrading initiatives.</em></p><p><em>By applying for this role, you consent to GMP Recruitment Services (S) Pte Ltds </em><a href=\"https://www.gmprecruit.com/legal/privacy-policy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>PDPA</em></a><em> and </em><a href=\"https://us-west-2.protection.sophos.com/?d=e2i.com.sg&u=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZTJpLmNvbS5zZy9wZHBhLw==&i=NThlNDdhOGMyYmI5N2YwZmQxZDk4NjQw&t=cWdqRFV0Uy80RjN3MDlSYmM1dS85VTRxVTRoYVlXdWFyWTYzaGlVS3k0TT0=&h=1ad0460f503340658fbeab159c31256f&s=AVNPUEhUT0NFTkNSWVBUSVaVGQEVMuPAipiPENS4aadnRg3RqoiWpHBKgNtumWhHjA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>e2is PDPA</em></a><em>.</em></p>",
